==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Howitzer
<hw>How"itz*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>haubitze</ets>, formerly <ets>hauffnitz</ets>, Bohem.
<ets>haufnice</ets>, orig., a sling.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A gun so short that the projectile, which was hollow,
could be put in its place by hand; a kind of mortar.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A short, light, largebore cannon,
usually having a chamber of smaller diameter than the rest of the bore,
and intended to throw large projectiles with comparatively small
charges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Howker</ent>⟦br⟧
